1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,520
I have to eat human flesh?

2
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:07,400
Fresh flesh from Old Master Khrua Phut

3
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:10,880
<i>is more powerful than</i>
<i>any sacred item in the world.</i>

4
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,640
<i>Nothing can resist it.</i>

5
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:16,080
<i>Not even Yiam's Klaikot Lek Lai.</i>

6
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:19,440
<i>I saw someone standing</i>
<i>on the water, staring at me,</i>

7
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,440
<i>before transforming</i>
<i>into a black crow and flying away.</i>

8
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,720
It might be the one
who tore out Duang's heart.

9
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,960
<i>You were going to destroy</i>
<i>the Lek Lai inside me? I never thought</i>

10
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:30,800
the woman I love would do this to me.

11
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,920
<i>I'm the lord</i>
<i>of dark sorcery now, aren't I?</i>

12
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,320
Of course you are.

13
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:39,840
Pun came to me on his own. He sold you out

14
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,600
What did you do to Old Master Khrua Phut?

15
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:55,720
That's impossible.
Old Master has powerful sorcery.

16
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:58,080
He'd never lose to a bastard like you!

17
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:04,520
- Ugh!
- Then go ask him in hell.

18
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,560
Damn it!

19
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,440
That night,

20
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,440
you were the only one who knew.

21
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:26,960
Ugh!

22
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,160
If you die,

23
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:34,480
everything ends.

24
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,360
And secrets

25
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:48,080
will stay secrets forever.

26
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,720
Yiam.

27
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,800
This is the same position
your father was in back then.

28
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:43,760
Yiam!

29
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:48,400
You won't get away from me!

30
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,960
Chaem, Niem.

31
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,440
We're here to help.

32
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:15,080
Hey! Watch out!

33
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:17,200
Watch out!

34
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,200
What the hell?

35
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,640
They call it "shooting fish in a barrel."

36
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,720
Petch!

37
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:30,000
I was minding my own business.

38
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:32,600
You two rushed in to die yourselves.

39
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,280
Good.

40
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:37,920
Now I can settle old scores
with all three of you at once.

41
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:45,680
I went to Pun's place. He wasn't there.
No idea where he went.

42
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:49,800
Maybe the governor's men caught him,
like Noree.

43
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:53,240
Oh, Pun…
He shouldn't have slipped up like this.

44
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,680
Do you realize what you did?

45
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:04,200
Destroying Lek Lai

46
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,880
is the same as destroying Yiam.

47
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:08,320
I'm sorry.

48
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:12,440
But I truly had no other choice.

49
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,560
I'm sorry too, about you and Yiam.

50
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,720
Forget it.

51
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:24,040
Our fate together only went this far.

52
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,920
I've made peace with it.

53
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,920
So where are you going?

54
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,160
I can't stay here anymore.

55
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,720
I'm going to find my father.

56
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,320
Search everywhere!

57
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,080
There's no one here, sir.

58
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:46,600
Go hunt them down. Go.

59
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:47,720
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

60
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:52,760
Whoa!

61
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:54,840
You let them slip away?

62
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,800
I apologize, Your Excellency.

63
00:06:57,400 --> 00:07:00,280
Get the hell out
before I lose my patience.

64
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:11,280
I wonder how long they can keep hiding.

65
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,040
If I catch them,

66
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:18,360
I'll split those rebels' skulls open
with my own hands.

67
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,480
I'm furious.

68
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,040
Last night, I almost killed Yiam,

69
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,080
but someone with sorcery saved him.

70
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,960
Who was it?

71
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,800
Old Master.

72
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:36,360
The body is impermanent.

73
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:40,159
What arises must pass.

74
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,840
Do not grieve.

75
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,840
Do not cling.

76
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:53,720
How can I defeat them, Old Master?

77
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,280
True strength

78
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:58,440
is inner strength.

79
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,680
No matter how shaken,

80
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,920
the heart remains steady and calm.

81
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:08,400
Conquering oneself
is the greatest victory.

82
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:11,720
Only a strong heart

83
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:14,680
allows one to overcome all things.

84
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,920
<i>Only a strong heart</i>

85
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,960
<i>allows one to overcome all things.</i>

86
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,560
They're hunting us down.

87
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:10,360
Pun and Noree are probably
being held at the governor's residence.

88
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:13,800
Yiwha, are you still
going to look for your father?

89
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,120
I'm going to the governor's residence.
We help Pun and Noree first.

90
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:20,840
Everything else can wait.

91
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:24,480
Let us go with you, Yiwha.

92
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,480
Noree.

93
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:36,800
- Pun!
- Noree!

94
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,000
Pun.

95
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,360
I'm here to help you, Noree.

96
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:43,440
What about the others?

97
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:46,680
Where are they?

98
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:51,480
Where is everyone, Pun?

99
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,440
Where is everyone?

100
00:10:55,160 --> 00:10:56,200
Pun.

101
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,440
Pun betrayed his friends

102
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:01,000
just to save your life, Noree.

103
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,640
Betrayed his friends?
What does that mean, Pun?

104
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,640
Pun?

105
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:12,920
It means

106
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:16,320
he stabbed his own friend in the back

107
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:18,320
and told me the secret.

108
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:25,160
That's not true, right?
You didn't betray your friends

109
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,840
to save me, right?

110
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:34,640
Pun!

111
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,920
What have you done, Pun?

112
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,760
Do you even realize what you've done?!

113
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:41,440
Noree, listen to me.

114
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,520
I had no choice, Noree.

115
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:48,440
If I hadn't, you would've died.

116
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:51,240
- I'd rather die!
- Noree.

117
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,480
I'd rather die!

118
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:57,160
Why would you throw away your dignity
and side with these people?

119
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,840
I'm so disappointed in you…

120
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,280
Where did the Pun I used to know go?

121
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:08,360
Noree… Noree…

122
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,800
Noree.

123
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,280
Noree, listen to me.

124
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:20,040
Noree.

125
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,840
When will you release Noree?

126
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:38,520
When I get Yiam and his people.

127
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:41,680
And how do I know you're not lying to me?

128
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:47,960
Pun, you don't get to bargain with me.

129
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,960
Stay obedient.

130
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:03,240
Then everything will be fine.

131
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:17,440
Lasor.

132
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:20,080
Good news or bad?

133
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,000
Good news.

134
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:37,120
Lasor.

135
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,920
You're hugging me like a kid.

136
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:49,720
So what brought you here?

137
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,160
Well…

138
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,720
I'd like to ask if I can stay with you?

139
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:58,640
The whole city is plastered
with wanted posters for me.

140
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,720
I've got nowhere to go.

141
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:04,200
Wherever I turn, someone's hunting me.

142
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:07,080
So I had to swallow my pride

143
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:09,200
and come seek shelter under you.

144
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:13,680
Of course. Why not?

145
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:17,320
Stay with me. I won't be lonely anymore.

146
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,400
- Really, Lasor?
- Of course.

147
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,360
Yiwha,

148
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:25,520
from now on,
you don't have to fear anyone.

149
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,120
No one will dare bully us again.

150
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:31,360
In this city,
your brother is the biggest man,

151
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:33,320
second only to

152
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:35,560
Phraya Kaipetch.

153
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:52,160
Stay here tonight.
If you need anything, tell me.

154
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:59,320
Isn't this a bit much?

155
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,520
Isn't it good?

156
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,800
Compensation for how hard
you and I used to live.

157
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:09,400
Way better than
that miserable shack at Chum Suea.

158
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,720
But at Chum Suea, we--

159
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:13,880
What about it?

160
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,240
Nothing.

161
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,320
Have you seen Dad at all?

162
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,400
Why do you ask?

163
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:32,440
I'm just worried about him.

164
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:34,360
I don't know how he is now.

165
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:41,600
I don't know.

166
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:44,080
But don't ask about this again.

167
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:50,400
Let's go.

168
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:54,920
Phraya Kaipetch orders you
to come see him now, sir.

169
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,000
Master.

170
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:19,960
Lasor,

171
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:25,000
I have three dangerous criminals
for you to punish.

172
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:26,960
Walk.

173
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:46,920
Uncle Niem!

174
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,680
Dad!

175
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,160
Wad and his gang

176
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:11,839
formed a bandit den,
robbing and slaughtering

177
00:17:11,920 --> 00:17:13,920
the family of Khun Yod Pakdee,

178
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,880
the village chief of Khuan Phra-ngam.

179
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:20,119
Only one sentence fits, death!

180
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:22,800
I did it.

181
00:17:24,119 --> 00:17:25,680
My son had nothing to do with it.

182
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:30,600
At last, you admit the truth, Wad.

183
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:52,600
Let's see

184
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:55,840
if my black-dog-blood-anointed blade

185
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:59,360
can cut your head off, Bandit Wad.

186
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:18,560
Lasor.

187
00:18:23,280 --> 00:18:24,440
Don't interfere!

188
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:28,280
Lasor.

189
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,680
Die!

190
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,680
A puppet?

191
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,640
<i>You think we're that stupid?</i>

192
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:49,040
<i>Niem, Chaem, and I</i>

193
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:51,480
<i>planned to sneak into</i>
<i>the governor's residence,</i>

194
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:53,360
<i>so you could catch us.</i>

195
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:54,720
I'm going in to see Lasor.

196
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:00,640
<i>Patimana phuttho ekakkatanang</i>

197
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:03,840
<i>rupa-sunyang nimittang itthiritti.</i>

198
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,640
<i>I molded dirt into a puppet</i>

199
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:10,000
<i>and use my spell to command it</i>
<i>to enter the residence in my place,</i>

200
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:13,400
<i>so I can rip off your mask</i>

201
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:17,320
<i>and let Lasor see, with his own eyes,</i>
<i>what his master truly is,</i>

202
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:21,120
<i>how vile and rotten you really are.</i>

203
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,040
Put it on.

204
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:32,680
<i>We waited until you sent men</i>
<i>to open the cell door,</i>

205
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:34,400
<i>and then we made our move.</i>

206
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:48,840
<i>Then Chaem and Niem</i>
<i>used Narai's transformation spell,</i>

207
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,640
<i>disguising themselves as your men.</i>

208
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,000
All of this

209
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:04,200
is Petch's evil scheme.

210
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:13,280
<i>Suja asu</i>

211
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:15,280
<i>jutannang.</i>

212
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,240
Die!

213
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:34,240
Niem!

214
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:35,840
Niem!

215
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:40,720
- Let go!
- Petch!

216
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:42,720
Petch!

217
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:51,680
Niem!

218
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:53,560
Niem!

219
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:55,320
Niem!

220
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,520
Uncle Niem!

221
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:01,000
Niem!

222
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:02,760
Petch.

223
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:06,000
<i>Sahassanetto devinto devarajjha</i>

224
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:08,160
<i>siridharo sangkhipita</i>

225
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:09,840
<i>vanatang maggang</i>

226
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:10,960
<i>khippang</i>

227
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:13,000
<i>savatthi makami.</i>

228
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:18,520
Wad,

229
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,880
Chaem, run!

230
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:34,280
Niem.

231
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,040
It's not too late to turn back.

232
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:48,720
I raised you.

233
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:52,800
I believe you weren't born rotten, Lasor.

234
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,200
Niem!

235
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,600
Uncle Niem. Uncle Niem.

236
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,840
Uncle Niem! Uncle Niem!

237
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:32,800
Niem used his last breath

238
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:37,000
to chant the distance-folding spell,
sending you and me out here.

239
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:43,640
Thank you, Niem,

240
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:47,200
for giving your life to save us.

241
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:51,080
Petch, I'm going to kill you.

242
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:56,680
Lasor is in his hands, Wad.

243
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,880
Think carefully. Don't be reckless.

244
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,120
I never thought

245
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:17,760
Lasor would have anything
to do with Yod's death.

246
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,800
I just hope Lasor finally opens his eyes

247
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:35,600
and sees Petch's true nature
for what it is.

248
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:18,560
Lasor,

249
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:20,920
if I let you live,

250
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:24,280
you'll become a thorn in my side.

251
00:25:08,760 --> 00:25:10,000
Did it work, Yiwha?

252
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:12,920
He agreed to let me stay.

253
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:16,600
So what do the two of us do next?

254
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:24,760
I'd say you look kind of cute like this.

255
00:25:26,120 --> 00:25:29,680
Cute my ass.
I can barely recognize myself.

256
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:33,600
This residence is full of captured slaves
brought in for labor.

257
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:35,600
They won't know who's who.

258
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:38,720
The two of us
will blend in with the slaves

259
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:41,240
and search for Pun and Noree.

260
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:57,400
Noree… Noree, wake up.

261
00:25:58,480 --> 00:26:00,960
Noree…

262
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:03,760
Wake up, Noree.

263
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:07,280
Why would you do something like this?

264
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:19,480
Noree…

265
00:26:21,760 --> 00:26:22,800
Noree…

266
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,080
Pun…

267
00:26:54,560 --> 00:26:56,120
I'm sorry, Pun.

268
00:27:03,480 --> 00:27:05,080
Noree died because of me.

269
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,360
What happened?

270
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:13,440
She chose death

271
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:17,760
but refused to become
a bargaining tool for your brother.

272
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:31,440
Your brother
isn't as good as you think, Yiwha.

273
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:38,920
Old Master.

274
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:42,760
How do I put out
the suffering in my heart?

275
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:46,680
If you can find the cause of suffering,
you can extinguish it.

276
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:50,160
All suffering gathers in the mind.

277
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:54,960
But my suffering is too much.

278
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:58,400
Fix your gaze on the mind.

279
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:01,800
Wherever there is suffering,
extinguish it there.

280
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:05,440
A mind freed from emotion,

281
00:29:05,520 --> 00:29:09,080
cut off from fabrication,
will be free of suffering.

282
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:12,080
If there is no suffering,

283
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:14,640
will I then be happy?

284
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:21,480
Happiness and suffering
are like the same snake.

285
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:26,480
The snake's head is suffering.
The snake's tail is happiness.

286
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:29,520
Whether you grab the head or the tail,

287
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:31,440
it can still bite,

288
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:36,880
because both head and tail
belong to the same snake,

289
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:39,760
craving and delusion.

290
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:57,760
Where are you going, my lady?

291
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:01,960
Where I go is none of your business.
I just want to get out of here.

292
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:06,520
You're not going anywhere.

293
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:08,200
Let go. Let go of me.

294
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:10,000
I said, let go.

295
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:15,360
<i>I raised you.</i>

296
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:19,880
I believe you weren't born rotten, Lasor.

297
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:25,560
Let go. Let go of me.

298
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,920
Lady Duen is trying to run away again.

299
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:36,840
Let her go.

300
00:30:39,440 --> 00:30:42,560
Your life is free.
You can go wherever you want.

301
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:45,320
Not like me.

302
00:30:47,120 --> 00:30:50,280
I'm stuck here. I can't go anywhere.

303
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:56,320
My lady,

304
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:00,440
if being with me

305
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:03,120
makes you unhappy,

306
00:31:05,360 --> 00:31:06,400
then go.

307
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:10,000
Leave me here alone.

308
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:15,920
Why didn't you come watch over me tonight?

309
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:26,480
I already set you free.

310
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:30,560
Do what you want. Go wherever you want.

311
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:34,560
Lasor,

312
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,320
what's wrong?

313
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,680
Tell me.

314
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:43,720
Since I was a child,

315
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:47,640
I wanted power.

316
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:50,520
I wanted to stand above others.

317
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:55,320
But now,

318
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,360
I have everything,

319
00:33:00,960 --> 00:33:04,040
wealth, power.

320
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:08,360
But it all comes

321
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:11,880
at the price of endless loss.

322
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:18,680
Now I have no one left…

323
00:33:20,680 --> 00:33:22,520
and even you were going to leave me.

324
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:27,880
I didn't want to leave you, Lasor.

325
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:33,080
I just want to forget
everything that happened here.

326
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:39,320
I don't have anyone left either.

327
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:44,840
My father

328
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:47,640
and my sister both died.

329
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,440
Everyone left me

330
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:57,280
and I had to face my suffering alone.

331
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:10,960
My lady…

332
00:34:13,120 --> 00:34:14,679
But you still have me.

333
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:18,239
I'll stay by your side.

334
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:21,760
I'll always be watching over you.

335
00:34:30,679 --> 00:34:32,840
But I've treated you so badly.

336
00:34:35,320 --> 00:34:38,320
Haven't you ever been angry?
Ever hated me?

337
00:34:59,200 --> 00:35:01,280
How could I hate the person I love?

338
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:32,800
A well-trained mind

339
00:36:32,880 --> 00:36:34,720
becomes strong and powerful.

340
00:36:35,680 --> 00:36:38,000
It can overcome all defilements

341
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:40,960
and bring happiness.

342
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:18,400
Lasor.

343
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,080
He's coming.

344
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:33,960
Yiam!

345
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:44,200
You'll die just like you want to.

346
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:53,520
Noree is dead?

347
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:58,920
Noree committed suicide
to end the problem.

348
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,120
We're…

349
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:04,120
too late.

350
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,400
Someone's attacking
the governor's residence!

351
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:18,920
- Yiam?
- Let's go.

352
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:35,120
Lasor!

353
00:40:43,200 --> 00:40:44,320
- Yiwha.
- Yiwha.

354
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:04,480
Yiwha.

355
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:06,720
Yiwha!

356
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:11,120
Yiwha.

357
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:16,960
Yiwha.

358
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:23,000
Yiwha.

359
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:58,680
Lasor.

360
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:02,040
Lasor.

361
00:42:02,120 --> 00:42:04,200
Is anyone here?

362
00:42:04,280 --> 00:42:06,640
Hurry. Get him back inside.

363
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:08,240
- Hurry up.
- Let's go.

364
00:42:08,760 --> 00:42:09,760
- Is he okay?
- Lasor.

365
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:40,200
Her pulse is getting weaker.

366
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,760
Please don't die, Yiwha.

367
00:42:55,120 --> 00:42:56,440
Come here.

368
00:42:58,600 --> 00:43:01,600
Why are you dragging me?
I'm going to Yiwha.

369
00:43:01,680 --> 00:43:03,520
Even if you go, it won't help.

370
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:05,600
Yiam won't let anything happen to her.

371
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:13,160
Right now, you have to do
what we came here for.

372
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:49,040
Lasor…

373
00:43:52,480 --> 00:43:53,800
don't die.

374
00:44:10,040 --> 00:44:12,880
Nui, help him. Please.

375
00:44:33,120 --> 00:44:34,160
Lasor.

376
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:39,680
- Yiwha.
- Yiwha.

377
00:44:44,880 --> 00:44:47,000
Those two share the same heart.

378
00:44:48,880 --> 00:44:50,400
If one dies,

379
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:53,600
the other dies too.

380
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:59,360
So getting rid of Lasor,
so he won't become a thorn in my side,

381
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:02,840
won't be difficult at all.

382
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:05,800
Your Excellency.

383
00:45:07,640 --> 00:45:08,600
What is it?

384
00:45:08,680 --> 00:45:11,240
Someone from the palace
is here to see you.

385
00:45:22,520 --> 00:45:24,840
There is an order from
Chao Phraya Khongkha Khet

386
00:45:25,520 --> 00:45:27,480
to summon Your Excellency to the capital.

387
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:31,200
What's the problem?

388
00:45:33,720 --> 00:45:36,920
His Excellency wishes to know
the reason Your Excellency

389
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:38,680
intended to build a railway.

390
00:45:41,880 --> 00:45:42,800
I believe

391
00:45:42,880 --> 00:45:45,960
you should hurry to see him.

392
00:46:09,360 --> 00:46:11,400
No matter how much medicine she takes,
she won't wake up.

393
00:46:11,480 --> 00:46:14,080
I have to find a way to save you, Yiwha.

394
00:46:32,040 --> 00:46:33,560
What do we do next, Wad?

395
00:46:35,040 --> 00:46:36,200
We wait.

396
00:46:39,600 --> 00:46:41,960
Wait until Lasor
finally comes to his senses.

397
00:46:45,360 --> 00:46:46,200
Who are you?

398
00:46:47,680 --> 00:46:48,880
Come out!

399
00:46:50,320 --> 00:46:52,000
Father Wad, it's me.

400
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:55,920
Nui?

401
00:46:57,160 --> 00:46:59,160
Lasor said you died
of jungle fever ages ago.

402
00:46:59,760 --> 00:47:01,600
Why haven't you moved on to the next life?

403
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:03,800
I…

404
00:47:05,240 --> 00:47:06,560
I'm worried about Lasor.

405
00:47:10,160 --> 00:47:12,040
What are you hiding from me, Nui?

406
00:47:12,840 --> 00:47:15,320
Lasor and Yiwha
are in bad shape right now.

407
00:47:15,400 --> 00:47:17,160
Please hurry and help them, Father Wad.

408
00:47:17,840 --> 00:47:19,080
What's wrong with my children?

409
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:24,800
While I'm gone,
watch the residence carefully.

410
00:47:24,880 --> 00:47:26,960
If anyone breaks in, kill them.

411
00:47:27,040 --> 00:47:27,880
Yes, sir.

412
00:47:53,400 --> 00:47:54,800
They're gone.

413
00:48:03,440 --> 00:48:06,320
We're captives brought here by force.

414
00:48:07,720 --> 00:48:09,440
We didn't see anything.

415
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:11,960
It's me.

416
00:48:15,320 --> 00:48:17,080
- Pun!
- Pun!

417
00:48:19,440 --> 00:48:21,040
What are you doing here?

418
00:48:28,360 --> 00:48:29,800
Go. This way.

419
00:48:40,480 --> 00:48:42,960
Talong and I
snuck in disguised as slave captives

420
00:48:43,040 --> 00:48:44,520
to help you and Noree.

421
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:48,720
I never thought

422
00:48:49,240 --> 00:48:51,600
Noree would take her own life.

423
00:48:55,680 --> 00:48:59,280
What about you? Why are you here?

424
00:49:02,120 --> 00:49:04,040
I came to put on an act and fool them,

425
00:49:04,680 --> 00:49:06,600
to gather evidence
to expose Phraya Kaipetch.

426
00:49:13,720 --> 00:49:15,120
Does Yiwha know about this?

427
00:49:17,040 --> 00:49:19,280
No matter what,
she's still Lasor's sister.

428
00:49:20,320 --> 00:49:22,320
I don't want to stir things up
and alert the enemy.

429
00:49:24,600 --> 00:49:25,760
Then it's settled.

430
00:49:26,280 --> 00:49:29,200
Let's use this chance
to find evidence and bring Kaipetch down.

431
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:42,400
When will you wake up, Yiwha?

432
00:49:51,040 --> 00:49:53,960
Bandit Wad? Uncle Chaem?

433
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:56,720
I came to help my daughter.

434
00:49:58,080 --> 00:49:59,280
I didn't come to harm anyone.

435
00:50:07,800 --> 00:50:08,760
Yiwha.

436
00:50:17,520 --> 00:50:19,320
Why is Yiwha like this?

437
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:24,720
Yiwha and Lasor are twins.
Their fates are bound.

438
00:50:25,480 --> 00:50:27,440
You used magic to attack Lasor's heart,

439
00:50:28,800 --> 00:50:30,800
so Yiwha suffered the effects as well.

440
00:50:33,040 --> 00:50:34,640
Yiwha's heartbeat is extremely weak.

441
00:50:35,800 --> 00:50:37,320
Lasor's must be the same.

442
00:50:38,960 --> 00:50:42,040
We need to find a cure
before the heart stops completely.

443
00:50:45,200 --> 00:50:47,400
I've tried nearly
every herbal formula I know,

444
00:50:48,080 --> 00:50:49,320
but nothing works.

445
00:50:50,360 --> 00:50:52,280
Ordinary herbs won't help.

446
00:50:56,240 --> 00:50:58,320
You need the pollen of the Twin Lotus.

447
00:51:00,160 --> 00:51:01,560
Twin Lotus pollen?

448
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:05,880
<i>The Twin Lotus,</i>

449
00:51:06,720 --> 00:51:09,520
<i>also known as Bua Kaew Bua Kwan,</i>

450
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:11,360
<i>grows in a pond atop Mount Khao Phrom.</i>

451
00:51:11,440 --> 00:51:15,000
<i>It's believed to possess medicinal</i>
<i>properties, able to nourish the heart</i>

452
00:51:15,080 --> 00:51:17,160
<i>and counter all kinds of dark sorcery.</i>

453
00:51:18,840 --> 00:51:20,800
I'll go get the Twin Lotus pollen myself.

454
00:51:21,440 --> 00:51:22,360
I'm going with you.

455
00:51:23,960 --> 00:51:27,080
If I let you go alone,
my daughter won't survive.

456
00:51:51,840 --> 00:51:54,320
Chaem,
while I'm heading up Mount Khao Phrom,

457
00:51:54,840 --> 00:51:56,320
please take care of Yiwha.

458
00:51:56,400 --> 00:51:58,680
Do not let the candle go out.

459
00:51:58,760 --> 00:52:00,440
Those wandering spirits are waiting

460
00:52:01,240 --> 00:52:03,040
for a chance to possess my daughter.

461
00:52:03,120 --> 00:52:04,360
Understood.

462
00:52:04,960 --> 00:52:05,800
Nui.

463
00:52:06,960 --> 00:52:09,720
This candle is for Lasor.
Guard his body carefully.

464
00:52:10,680 --> 00:52:11,520
Yes, Father Wad.

465
00:52:20,720 --> 00:52:21,880
But what if we

466
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:26,120
can't find the Twin Lotus
or don't make it back in time?

467
00:52:28,400 --> 00:52:29,760
Then the heart will stop beating,

468
00:52:32,440 --> 00:52:35,800
and the bodies of Yiwha and Lasor
will slowly rot away.

469
00:52:54,600 --> 00:52:56,640
It's broad daylight.
Why are you lighting a candle?

470
00:52:57,520 --> 00:53:00,800
This candle is vital to Lasor's life.

471
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:02,200
Until he wakes up,

472
00:53:03,120 --> 00:53:05,400
it must not go out no matter what.

473
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:09,160
- Why?
- Don't ask so many questions.

474
00:53:10,760 --> 00:53:12,480
Just do as I say.

475
00:53:59,960 --> 00:54:01,000
The key?

476
00:54:11,960 --> 00:54:13,640
I've got it.

477
00:54:32,920 --> 00:54:34,560
THE GOVERNOR OF THA KHIRI GRANTS
PERMISSION TO DAMONT, NOËL, AND HENRI

478
00:54:34,640 --> 00:54:36,520
TO FREELY ESTABLISH OPIUM DENS,
GAMBLING HOUSES, AND BROTHELS,

479
00:54:36,600 --> 00:54:38,120
WITH 30 PERCENT OF ALL REVENUES
PAYABLE AS TAX TO THE GOVERNOR.

480
00:54:39,320 --> 00:54:40,400
Found it.

481
00:54:43,920 --> 00:54:44,920
This is it,

482
00:54:45,640 --> 00:54:48,120
the evidence to expose Phraya Kaipetch.

483
00:54:50,920 --> 00:54:52,120
Good.

484
00:54:52,200 --> 00:54:56,280
Then we'll expose
all his corruption to the townspeople.

485
00:54:59,960 --> 00:55:01,120
Who's there?

486
00:56:09,080 --> 00:56:10,360
What?

487
00:56:10,440 --> 00:56:12,880
I kind of want you
to stay like this a little longer.

488
00:56:17,800 --> 00:56:19,160
Is this really the time?

489
00:56:48,160 --> 00:56:51,360
If we save Yiwha,
Lasor will wake up too, right?

490
00:56:52,640 --> 00:56:55,080
Yiwha and Lasor share the same heart.

491
00:56:55,160 --> 00:56:58,600
If one dies, the other dies.
If one survives, the other survives.

492
00:57:00,000 --> 00:57:03,280
Then no matter how despicable Lasor is,

493
00:57:03,360 --> 00:57:04,760
I can't do anything to him at all.

494
00:57:07,960 --> 00:57:10,840
That's why I tried to cleanse
the dark sorcery from his body,

495
00:57:11,480 --> 00:57:13,160
erase all his memories,

496
00:57:13,960 --> 00:57:16,040
and send him somewhere no one knows him.

497
00:57:17,360 --> 00:57:18,880
That's no different from helping him

498
00:57:19,400 --> 00:57:21,440
escape the crimes he's committed.

499
00:57:24,880 --> 00:57:27,360
Or would you rather see
Yiwha meet the same end as Lasor?

500
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:34,080
I suppose
I'll have to go down to Tha Khiri

501
00:57:34,760 --> 00:57:36,880
and see it with my own eyes.

502
00:57:36,960 --> 00:57:38,960
Who dares poke the bear?

503
00:57:39,040 --> 00:57:40,640
- Talong, run!
- Talong!

504
00:57:40,720 --> 00:57:41,600
Chang!

505
00:57:42,840 --> 00:57:44,200
<i>We'll never be able to kill them all</i>

506
00:57:44,920 --> 00:57:47,160
as long as Phraya Kaipetch is still alive.

507
00:57:47,240 --> 00:57:49,360
Working together to eliminate Petch
is more important.

508
00:57:51,000 --> 00:57:53,120
I want you to join me.

509
00:57:54,000 --> 00:57:54,840
‪That's the lotus pond.

510
00:57:56,320 --> 00:57:59,960
I was almost killed by Yiam's spell.
Who saved me?

511
00:58:03,720 --> 00:58:05,200
May I sleep with you?

512
00:58:05,280 --> 00:58:06,520
I'll have you ordained

513
00:58:07,160 --> 00:58:08,440
and send you to Lanka.

514
00:58:08,520 --> 00:58:11,120
I won't be a pawn
in your revenge ever again.

515
00:58:14,080 --> 00:58:16,200
You'll regret this, Lasor.

516
00:59:00,880 --> 00:59:02,560
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
